
// The code snippet dynamically adds nodes from the [headers] node within [.arguments] to the existing [headers] node in the current context. It uses [get-nodes] to retrieve all header nodes from [.arguments] and appends them to the destination headers node, allowing for the customization of HTTP request headers based on input arguments.
add:x:+/+/*/headers
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/headers/*
